  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for ceph",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for ceph fixes the following issues:\n\n- ceph was updated to 15.2.11-83-g8a15f484c2:\n  * CVE-2021-20288: Fixed unauthorized global_id reuse (bsc#1183074).\n  * disk gets replaced with no rocksdb/wal (bsc#1184231).\n  * BlueStore handles huge(\u003e4GB) writes from RocksDB \n    to BlueFS poorly, potentially causing data corruption (bsc#1183899).\n\nThis update was imported from the SUSE:SLE-15-SP2:Update update project.",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
